martin marietta corp will try again 
tonight to conduct the thricedelayed launch its first commerical 
titan 3 rocket with british and japanese communications satellites 
the flight was scrubbed monday night just five minutes before 
the planned liftoff when weather balloon data indicated winds 
27000 feet above the launch area were too strong 
the winds aloft are not acceptable launch commentator bob 
gordon said in announcing the postponement 
the launch was rescheduled for 720 pm tonight it was 
postponed twice earlier this month by weather and technical 
problems 
the titan 3 is to boost into orbit communications satellites for 
a japanese company and the british ministry of defense 
the japanese communications satellite co and the british 
government are sharing the 125 million cost of the rocket and 
launch services provided by martin marietta 
