morning hope police chief richard thomas said 
in addition officials said hotels in the area were full while 
other motorists spent the night in their vehicles walmarts 
parking lot was full of 18wheelers thomas said 
some 70 school districts across arkansas remained closed tuesday 
because of the inclement weather state office workers were under 
the states inclement weather policy which gives nonessential 
administrative workers until 10 am to arrive without being 
deducted leave time 
many northern georgia counties kept their schools closed 
although most atlanta area schools reopened after being closed 
monday 
officials in griffin ga said ice brought tree limbs down on 
power lines there cutting electricity to large sections of the 
city for as long as two hours 
ice on roads was blamed for accidents around metropolitan 
atlanta and athens and police blocked off several interstate 
highway ramps that were littered with cars and trucks unable to 
cross slick spots 
treacherous driving conditions in north carolina caused at least 
one death and scores of traffic accidents and dozens of schools 
and business closed 
rain fell from the remainder of georgia into northern florida 
and northern alabama and was scattered along the gulf of mexico 
coast 
in the mountains of southeastern wyoming wind blew at 50 to 60 
mph near arlington and near vedauwoo 
a 200mile stretch of the mississippi river from st louis to 
