about 60 percent of the 195 miles of missouri river north of 
omaha neb to the gavins point dam was frozen over tuesday 
forming ice jams that reduced the amount of water flowing 
downstream to towns and power plants 
the river level was within one foot of the level at which some 
power plants would be unable to operate because their water intake 
systems would no longer work said chet worm chief of the 
reservoir regulation section of the corps missouri river district 
