a bartlett giamatti baseball lover and former president of 
yale university whose short tenure as baseball commissioner was 
dominated by the investigation and banishment of pete rose at age 
51 of a heart attack 
georges simenon prolific writer of more than 200 novels 
including 80 featuring the popular inspector maigret his books 
were translated into 55 languages and sold more than 500 million 
copies worldwide making him perhaps the most widely read author of 
the 20th century age 86 
robert penn warren the nations first poet laureate winner of 
three pulitzer prizes for fiction and poetry rooted in his native 
south age 84 
irving berlin whose songs such as cheek to cheek easter 
parade white christmas and god bless america were the 
essence of american popular music age 101 
ferdinand e marcos ruled the philippines for more than 20 
years but became an unwanted exile after being ousted in 1986 age 
72 
august a busch jr patriarch of the worlds largest brewing 
dynasty and president of baseballs st louis cardinals age 90 
</TEXT>
