for his roles as a fighting man in such films as the guns of 
navarone he also was honored with british knighthood as a 
mainstay of the classical theater age 76 
mary mccarthy critic and novelist whose iceclear observations 
of politics and literature made her one of americas longtime 
literary stars age 77 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
vladimir horowitz titan of the keyboard who brought 
controlled thunder to the piano dazzling the world for 60 
years age 85 
charles beck comic book artist who created captain marvel the 
superhero who came to life at the word shazam age 79 
clement f haynesworth jr whose nomination to the supreme 
court in 1969 was rejected by the senate because of his business 
practices and his views on minorities age 77 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
alvin ailey dancer and choreographer whose dynamic style 
introduced black american music and traditions into modern dance 
and helped transform it into a popular art form at age 58 of a 
blood disorder 
sammy fain oscarwinning composer whose classic love ballads 
included love is a many splendored thing and ill be seeing 
you age 87 
john payne leading man who starred in hollywood musicals with 
alice faye and betty grable and in dramas such as miracle on 34th 
street age 77 
andrei sakharov soviet dissident nobel peace prize winner and 
brilliant scientist who built the soviet hydrogen bomb risked his 
status as a national hero to openly challenge the government on 
behalf of disarmament and human rights age 68 
</TEXT>
