of a 50 million note to the asbestos victims trust fund created 
by its bankruptcy reorganization according to the manville 
personal injury settlement trust 
in a filing with the securities and exchange commission on 
monday the trust said it had been exploring ways to improve 
liquidity after a plan for manville to repurchase 500 million of 
its preferred stock fell through earlier this month 
