<TEXT>
employees have been living with uncertainty at 
trans world ailines inc ever since carl icahn bought the carrier 
in 1986 but now they believe the handwriting on the wall is 
becoming clearer 
twa which began the decade as one of the nations largest 
airlines is in serious danger of disappearing in the early 1990s 
industry analysts and workers say 
the airline is saddled with 27 billion in debt its 218 
airplanes are among the oldest used by major carriers and pilots 
mechanics and flight attendants are frustrated and disillusioned 
about their future 
on monday twa announced plans to sell its chicagotolondon 
route and four gates and a dormant maintenance facility at 
chicagos ohare airport to american airlines for 195 million a 
move that shocked and angered workers 
the sale is subject to regulatory approval 
its very difficult to see how selling a route to a competitor 
can be beneficial said herb johnson president of the machinists 
unions local 1650 in kansas city selling the london route just 
doesnt compute 
johnson who heads the airlines largest union local said 
workers cant help but wonder if theyre going to have a carrier to 
work for in 1990 and its particularly upsetting to see the route 
go to a fierce rival like american 
american is a tough competitor everyone knows that once they 
get in your markets theyll blow your doors off johnson said 
market share is everything in this business and when you start 
reducing that youre in trouble 
icahn said the proposed sale will help restore profitability at 
twa which has already lost 117 million for the first nine months 
of 1989 and is expected to lose between 230 million to 300 
million for the year 
twa is headquartered in mt kisco ny but has one of its 
largest hub operations in st louis 
icahn who took the company private last year said the company 
will need the money from the sale to make it through a slump in 
business thats already under way and to survive an industry 
consolidation in the mid90s 
there is a time to invest and a time to be cautious and now 
is the time to be cautious icahn told employees in threepage 
letter on the state of twa 
but no one at twa or in the airline industry seems to believe 
that caution is what prompted the sale to american 
some analysts believe icahn is trying to raise more money to buy 
additional stock in usx corp a company hes been rumored to be 
interested in buying for years 
in fact on tuesday icahn received permission from the federal 
trade commission to acquire a bigger stake at least 25 percent 
of usx a pittsburghbased steel and energy company 
icahn currently owns 34 million or 136 percent of usxs 
outstanding common shares 
theres also speculation that icahn has found an airline that 
wants to buy twa and icahn is now trying to streamline the airline 
to help avoid any antitrust violations 
this sale could be consistent with a lot of different theories 
about whats goig to happen to twa said paul turk an analyst 
with avmark inc an aviation consulting firm based in arlington 
va 
kent scott chairman of the twa unit of the air line pilots 
association said he believes mondays proposed sale is the 
beginning of the complete liquidation of the airline 
i think hes testing the water of opposition in the regulatory 
agencies and if he gets this one through he can use it as a 
precedent when he proposes others said scott who is based in 
st louis 
the next routes for sale may be the coasttocoast flights new 
york to los angeles and san francisco scott said meanwhile 
scott said he expects the three boeing 747 airliners used by twa to 
fly from chicago to london to be up for sale once the american deal 
goes through 
the pilots union will encourage federal regulators to quash the 
deal scott said 
whatever the reason for mondays proposed sale analysts agree 
with icahn that the airline industry has been struggling recently 
with higher costs and slackening demand for air travel 
twa hasnt been performing well and the whole industry hasnt 
been doing too well either said mark daugherty a stock analyst 
at dean witter reynolds in new york this mondays sale 
surgically removes a route that wasnt that important but its 
hard to say what it means 
