boeing co faced a new labor threat tuesday from 
the engineers and scientists who play a crucial role in designing 
its planes less than a month after a crippling machinists strike 
ended at the aerospace giant 
in ballots counted monday night those members of the seattle 
professional engineering employees association voted 69 percent to 
reject a threeyear contract offer from the worlds largest 
commercial airline builder 
although members also voted by 52 percent not to authorize their 
negotiators to call a strike the union said it might be well into 
1990 before the contract talks resume 
our executive director has been in touch with the director of 
labor relations at boeing and weve made known our availability at 
any time said dan mahoney union general counsel 
however it appears the rejection was quite a surprise to 
company negotiators and they werent prepared for it so they have 
to assemble their negotiating team 
