<TEXT>
plans to trade gold options and options on oat 
futures contracts at two chicago futures exchanges were approved 
tuesday by federal regulators 
the commodity futures trading commission which oversees the 
futures industry approved the two plans unanimously 50 
a futures contract is an agreement to buy or sell a commodity 
like oats at a specified price by a specified date 
one of the approved proposals was for the chicago mercantile 
exchange to trade physical gold options 
that will give the holder of a cme gold option contract the 
right to buy or sell 100 troy ounces of gold at a specified strike 
price on the delivery date 
a strike price is the price at which an option holder can choose 
to exercise the right to buy or sell the underlying futures 
contract 
the contract is designed to be a hedging instrument whereby 
producers buyers and sellers of gold can lock in a favorable price 
for transactions at a later date 
the cftc also approved a proposal by the chicago board of trade 
for trading options in its oats futures contracts holders of such 
options will be able to buy or sell oat futures contracts on any 
trading day prior to the contracts expiration the trading months 
will be based on the underlying futures delivery months of march 
may july september and december 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

