<TEXT>
american airlines announced its anticipated deal 
with eastern airlines tuesday saying it would buy latin american 
routes and certain other assets from easterns parent company for 
471 million 
the deal with texas air corp in one stroke makes american a 
major international carrier giving it 20 destinations in 15 
central and south american countries 
in addition to the latin american routes american also gets a 
miamitolondon route from easterns sister carrier continental 
airlines and easterns routes to toronto from miami and tampa 
fla and its unused route authority from miami to madrid spain 
plus american gets continental and eastern slots at john f 
kennedy international airport in new york and eastern slots at new 
yorks laguardia airport miami international airport washington 
national airport ohare international airport in chicago and san 
juan puerto rico 
american and continental also agreed to a gate exchange at 
dallasfort worth international airport 
the deal had been rumored to be imminent for more than a week as 
eastern seeks cash to help it emerge from bankruptcy protection 
the bankruptcy court and government regulators have to approve the 
sale which is a key part of easterns reorganization plan 
separately eastern said it will sell the 14 lockheed l1011 
aircraft currently used to serve the latin american routes 
american which has spent billions of dollars on new jets recently 
said it wasnt interested in the l1011s they range in age from 
125 years to 17 years 
besides the routes and landing slots texas air agreed to drop a 
1 billion lawsuit against sabre american parent amr corps 
computer reservations systems texas air subsidiary continental 
airlines claimed sabre which is used by travel agents to book 
passengers and is the largest such us system unfairly favored 
american flights 
although deal between american and eastern had been expected 
negotiations broke down in august apparently over the disposition 
of the lawsuit 
analyst helane becker at shearson lehman hutton inc said 
american would have a leg up on european carriers trying to serve 
the growing latin american market because american could route 
flights from europe through its miami hub cutting three hours off 
the trip 
this transaction will allow our company to continue building 
our international network and it will make the us a strong 
competitor in central and south america by linking that region to 
americans extensive route system chairman robert l crandall 
said in a press release 
american called a news conference for miami wednesday morning to 
discuss the deal which it said will create about 2000 airport and 
reservation jobs in that city during the next five years 
texas air said eastern would realize 349 million from the sale 
while continental 1025 million and system one texas airs 
reservation system 195 million for the telecommunications 
equipment needed to service the routes 
the sale of these assets will enable eastern airlines to 
continue on its course of successfully rebuilding as a smaller and 
stronger airline from the future with its operation at its atlanta 
hub texas air said in a prepared statement 
eastern and continental will continue to operate the routes 
until american is ready to take them over texas air said 
